      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De honore</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e112">Plus in hoc mundo honor, quam despectio occupat;
              magis prosperitatis sublimitas, quam necessitatis adversitas gravat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e127">Transit, quod extollitur; permanet, quod
              punitur; et qui honoratur in via, in perventione damnabitur; et quasi per amoena prata
              ad carcerem pervenit, qui per praesentis vitae prospera ad interitum tendit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e142">Tantorum pondera unusquisque sustinere
              compellitur, quantis hoc mundo principatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e157">Tumoris elatio, non ordo potestatis in crimine
              est. Potentiam enim Deus tribuit, elationem vero potentiae malitia nostrae mentis
              invenit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e173">Numerari culpae nequeunt, quae habendae
              potestatis amore perpetrantur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e188">Penset quisque quid subjectus egerit, et repente
              cognoscet si praelatus bona agere, quae proposuerit, possit: quia nequaquam valet in
              culmine humilitatem discere, qui in imis positus non desiit superbire.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e203">Saepe suscepta cura regiminis cor per diversa
              intuendo diverberat; et impar quisque invenitur ad singula, dum confusa mente
              dividitur ad multa.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e210">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e218">In alto loco positis, saepe dum exterius ab
              hominibus honor tribuitur, ad ima animus mergitur, quia curis discerpentibus
              gravatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e225">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e233">Nec cuilibet, favente gratia, ultra quam
              meretur, impartior: nec ulli hoc, quod sui juris est, ambitu stimulante denegabo; sed
              fratres meos honorare per omnia cupio, sicque studeo honore singulos subvehi, dum non
              sit quod alteri jure ab altero possit opponi.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e240">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e248">Nec honorem reputo, in quo fratres meos honorem
              suum perdere cognosco.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e256">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e264">Minorem major praecedit, sicut honore, ita et
              crimine.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e271">Isidorus, <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e279">Saepe per honores quorumdam mutantur et mores;
              et quos ante conglutinatos charitate habuerunt, postquam ad culmen honoris venerint,
              amicos habere despiciunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e286">Isidorus, <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e294">Non debet honoris ducatum suscipere, qui nescit
              subditos tramite vitae melioris praeire. Neque enim quisque ad hoc praeficitur, ut
              subditorum culpas corrigat, et ipse vitiis serviat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e301">Augustinus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e309">Non cogito in ecclesiasticis honoribus tempora
              ventosa transigere; sed cogito me Principi pastorum omnium rationem de commissis
              ovibus redditurum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e316">Augustinus, <title>de Pastoribus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e324">Quisquis ita praepositus est, ut in eo quod
              praepositus est, gaudeat, et honorem suum quaerat, et commoda sua sola respiciat; se
              pascit, non oves.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e339" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e331">Bernardus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e339">Potestate accepta malle in malo quam in bono
              uti, abuti est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e345">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e355" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e347">Bernardus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e355">Non dignum est, ut inde exigas honorem, unde
              refugis laborem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e360">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e370" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e362">Bernardus, <title>super Cantica</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e370">Fratres, revereamur episcopos, sed vereamur
              labores eorum. Si labores pensamus, non affectamus honores.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-d1e375">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e382" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Rd1e377">Glossa</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e35609-Qd1e382">Quanto gradus altior, tanto casus
              gravior.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
